sentences: Jair-Rôhm Parker Wells (born October 13, 1958) is an American electric bassist.
He lived in Stockholm, Sweden, from 1985 until 2017.
He lived in Stockholm, Sweden, from 1985 until 2017.
In 2017, he was in residence at EMS in Stockholm where he began work on his opera #blacbuc.
Raised in southern Germany, Jair-Rôhm moved to New York in 1978.
In 1980 he returned to New York and started work-study with saxophonist Ken Simon.
In 1982 he founded his  experimental music theater group Glass Thought Theater Ensemble.
Between 1982 and 1983 he was composer in residence at the New York Theater Ensemble, writing and producing a trilogy of progressive "operas".
He received a Meet the Composer grant in 1983.
After touring the United States for a year with a pop music band, he attended Tulane University in New Orleans.
During the next year, he lived in New Jersey and was a founding member of the New Brunswick Jazz Musician's Collective, for which he composed several works for ensembles.
